.TH LOGGERX 1 "February 2026" "loggerx" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
loggerx \- colorized terminal logger with syslog output
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B loggerx
.I LEVEL
.I MESSAGE...
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B loggerx
prints log entries with a UTC timestamp and level styling, then forwards a raw
message to syslog via
.BR logger (1).

It supports multi-line messages and infers application identity from the parent
process unless overridden via environment.
.SH LEVELS
0/EMERGENCY, 1/ALERT, 2/CRITICAL, 3/ERROR, 4/WARNING,
5/NOTICE, 6/INFO, 7/DEBUG, 9/SUCCESS
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B APP_NAME
Overrides inferred application name in logs.
.TP
.B APP_PID
Overrides inferred PID tag in logs (for forwarding workflows such as et/rc).
.TP
.B LOG_TO_FILE
If set to
.B true
also appends formatted output to
.BR LOG_FILE .
.TP
.B LOG_FILE
Path used when
.B LOG_TO_FILE=true
.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Show help text and exit.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
Invalid log level.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B loggerx INFO "service started"
.TP
.B loggerx 6 "service started"
.TP
.B APP_NAME=myapp loggerx WARNING "cache miss"
.TP
.B LOG_TO_FILE=true LOG_FILE=/tmp/app.log loggerx ERROR "request failed"
.SH AUTHOR
Alex Atkinson and contributors.
